---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Authentication" description="Learn about GoodIssues API authentication and API key types.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Authentication</h1>
  <p class="text-muted mb-8">All API requests require authentication using API keys.</p>

  <!-- API Key Types -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">API Key Types</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      GoodIssues provides two types of API keys with different permission levels:
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-sm border border-base-300/50 bg-base-200/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <code class="text-primary font-mono text-sm">pk_*</code>
          <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-primary/10 text-primary">Public Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted">
          <strong class="text-base-content">Read-only access.</strong> Use public keys for applications that only need to read data, such as dashboards, reports, or integrations that display issue information.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-muted">
          Permissions: <code class="text-success">GET</code> requests only
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-4 rounded-sm border border-base-300/50 bg-base-200/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <code class="text-primary font-mono text-sm">sk_*</code>
          <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-warning/10 text-warning">Secret Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted">
          <strong class="text-base-content">Full read/write access.</strong> Use secret keys for applications that need to create, update, or delete resources. Keep these keys secure and never expose them in client-side code.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-muted">
          Permissions: <code class="text-success">GET</code> <code class="text-primary">POST</code> <code class="text-warning">PATCH</code> <code class="text-error">DELETE</code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Using API Keys -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Using API Keys</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      Include your API key in the <code class="text-primary">Authorization</code> header using the Bearer scheme:
    </p>

    <div class="rounded-sm border border-base-300 bg-base-200/90 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-base-300/50">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-muted">HTTP Header</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-muted">Authorization:</span>
        <span class="text-primary ml-2">Bearer sk_live_your_api_key_here</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content mt-6 mb-3">Example Request</h3>
    <div class="rounded-sm border border-base-300 bg-base-200/90 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-base-300/50">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-muted">curl</span>
      </div>
      <pre class="p-4 font-mono text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="text-muted">curl https://api.goodissues.dev/api/v1/issues \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk_live_your_api_key_here" \
  -H "Accept: application/json"</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Multi-tenant Access -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Multi-tenant Access</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      API keys are scoped to a specific account membership. This means:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <svg class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        <span>Each API key can only access resources within its associated account</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <svg class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        <span>To access multiple accounts, create separate API keys for each</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <svg class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        <span>Users can belong to multiple accounts with different API keys for each</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Error Responses -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Error Responses</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      Authentication errors return appropriate HTTP status codes:
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-sm border border-base-300/50 bg-base-200/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <code class="text-error font-mono text-sm">401 Unauthorized</code>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted">
          No API key provided, or the API key is invalid/expired.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-2 rounded bg-base-200 p-2 font-mono text-xs">
          <span class="text-muted" set:html={'{"errors": {"detail": "Unauthorized"}}'} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-4 rounded-sm border border-base-300/50 bg-base-200/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <code class="text-warning font-mono text-sm">403 Forbidden</code>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted">
          The API key doesn't have permission for the requested action (e.g., using a <code class="text-primary">pk_*</code> key for a write operation).
        </p>
        <div class="mt-2 rounded bg-base-200 p-2 font-mono text-xs">
          <span class="text-muted" set:html={'{"errors": {"detail": "Forbidden"}}'} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Security Best Practices -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Security Best Practices</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <svg class="size-5 text-success mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
        </svg>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-base-content">Never expose secret keys in client-side code.</strong>
          <p class="mt-1">Use <code class="text-primary">sk_*</code> keys only in server-side applications or secure environments.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <svg class="size-5 text-success mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
        </svg>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-base-content">Use environment variables.</strong>
          <p class="mt-1">Store API keys in environment variables, not in code or version control.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <svg class="size-5 text-success mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
        </svg>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-base-content">Use the principle of least privilege.</strong>
          <p class="mt-1">Use <code class="text-primary">pk_*</code> keys when read-only access is sufficient.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <svg class="size-5 text-success mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
        </svg>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-base-content">Rotate keys periodically.</strong>
          <p class="mt-1">Regularly rotate API keys and immediately revoke any that may have been compromised.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Next steps -->
  <section class="pt-6 border-t border-base-300/30">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Next Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <a href="/docs/api/projects/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">
        <svg class="size-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        Explore the Projects API
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/api/issues/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">
        <svg class="size-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        Explore the Issues API
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
